& [MeasuredObjectCandidateCriteriaSpecification] is a non-mutating admission contract
  + [source_snapshot_uuid] is 9c480377-8dd9-41b0-9405-942ebdb3d754
  + [manifest_uuid] is 7f99c312-abe9-4c7e-90d7-3922fbf17593
  + [canonical_specification_uuid] is 602cbb2f-8cfa-48e6-a95d-f011fd14cfbe
  + [project_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis
  + [active_authority_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop
  + [purpose] is define admission gates for future source-defined measured objects
  + [not_purpose] is new computation, proof, zero certification, branch reopening, staging, committing, broad .sop mutation, denser scans, more labels, more windows, or more offsets
  + [proof_status] is criteria_not_rh_evidence

& [AdmissionGate] is required_before_math_processing
  + [gate_source] is raw source preserved plus canonical specification before analysis or implementation
  + [gate_purpose] is a named question with purpose beyond curiosity, density, novelty, or visual resemblance
  + [gate_dense_node_parentage] is one primary dense node plus explicit support lanes and governance lane
  + [gate_whole_field_relevance] is relation to pi(x), theta(x), psi(x), Lambda(n), Euler/log-derivative, explicit residuals, zeta-reference behavior, or another named whole-field object
  + [gate_identity_boundary] is inside, outside, not-it boundary, related periphery, and suspected external/internal fabric status
  + [gate_existing_evidence] is a cited record set showing why the object is warm enough to pursue
  + [gate_method_contract] is deterministic inputs, outputs, finite metric, comparison contract, and expected artifact path
  + [gate_contradiction_handling] is what result would weaken, retire, or rescope the candidate
  + [gate_restraint] is explicit check against reopening paused branches by density alone
  + [gate_exit] is a definite conclusion condition for the bounded pass
  + [gate_truth_boundary] is finite measurement only; no proof, disproof, zero certification, RH evidence, or critical-line authority

& [CandidateStatusSet] is classification_contract
  + [candidate_rejected] is fails a required gate
  + [candidate_support_only] is useful as orientation but not admitted for computation
  + [candidate_source_needed] is promising but lacks preserved source or canonical specification
  + [candidate_spec_ready] is source and specification exist but deterministic tool contract is still missing
  + [candidate_ready_for_deterministic_processing] is all gates pass and a bounded math-processing contract exists

  = must: treat all gates as conjunctive before computation
  = must: keep special-prime observations subordinate to whole-field objects
  = must: keep Lambda overlay, landmark overlay, explicit/Euler bridge, and shell expansion pauses active unless a new source-defined purpose passes the gate
  = must: report failure gates rather than patching them with inference
  - never: promote a candidate because it is merely interesting, dense, sparse, repeated, or aesthetically suggestive
  - never: use this criteria contract as permission for numerical work without a later candidate-specific source/spec

& [MeasuredObjectCandidateCriteriaSJS] is the specification justification trace
  + [processed_stage_set] is source_preserved, delineated, canonicalized, constraint_checked, justified, and admission_gate_scoped
  + [processing_result] is accepted_measured_object_admission_contract
  + [reasoning_result] is continuous RH walking needs a way to keep inquiry open while preventing ungoverned computation; admission gates make the next measured object selectable without turning periphery heat into proof pressure

(measured_object_candidate_criteria) :admission gate: /source, purpose, node, boundary, method, contradiction, exit/ |proof claims|
  + [inside] is criteria for future measured-object selection
  + [boundary] is no computation, no proof inference, no branch reopening, no staging, no commit
  |outside| RH proof, disproof, zero certification, critical-line authority, numerical scans, and identity fusion
